para_sentences.para_0: At this point, you should be able to answer all of the following questions.
para_sentences.para_1: You should now be able to create and use dictionaries, as well as create and use sets.
para_sentences.para_2: If you are unsure of any of these answers, take some time to review the course materials. Feel free to post questions in Piazza or Teams. Next week's lessons will be easier if you have invested in mastering this week's learning outcomes.
para_sentences.para_3: Check the Explorations and Task List in the Lesson 8 - Overview to review learning materials and make sure you have completed all required activities for this week.

ul_0: What is a dictionary? How is it different from a list?
In what ways can you modify a dictionary?
What are some other operations/functions/methods for dictionaries?
What is a set? How is it different from a list?
What are some of the operations/functions/methods for sets?
